# Cashier-less Billing System Architecture

This app implements a smart billing system where products taken or returned are automatically added or subtracted from a customer's bill using computer vision.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Please clarify the camera setup for the application:
> 
> 1. **Option A (Self-Checkout App)**: The customer holds their mobile phone, and the app uses the phone camera to detect products being picked up or put back.
> 2. **Option B (Smart Shelf like Amazon Go)**: There are fixed cameras on the shelves tracking the products, and the app is just a dashboard for the customer to view their bill in real-time.
> 
> The proposed architecture below assumes **Option A** (a mobile-friendly Web App that accesses the device camera). Please confirm if this is what you want!

## Proposed Changes

We will build the system in two parts: a React/Vite Frontend and a Python/FastAPI Backend.

### Frontend App (Vite + React)
- **Features**:
  - Login/Customer ID Entry surface.
  - Camera access page (`getUserMedia` API) that streams frames to the backend or processes them via a lightweight in-browser model.
  - Cart dashboard showing the current bill, updating in real-time as items are added or removed.
- **Tech Stack**: React, Vanilla CSS for modern and sleek styling.

#### [NEW] `frontend/src/App.jsx`
Main layout and routing between Login, Camera view, and Cart view.

#### [NEW] `frontend/src/CameraView.jsx`
Handles WebRTC or frame streaming to the backend for computer vision processing.

#### [NEW] `frontend/src/Cart.jsx`
Displays the real-time bill and current cart items.

---

### Backend System (FastAPI + OpenCV)
- **Features**:
  - Exposes REST/WebSocket API for the frontend app.
  - Handles the computer vision logic (mocked or simple OpenCV initially) to detect "pick up" vs "put down" actions.
  - Manages the state of the cart for each `customer_id`.
- **Tech Stack**: Python, FastAPI, WebSockets (for real-time cart updates), OpenCV.

#### [NEW] `backend/main.py`
Endpoints for customer sessions and WebSocket connection for camera frame processing.

#### [NEW] `backend/vision.py`
Logic to process frames and determine if a product has been added or removed from the view.

#### [NEW] `backend/cart.py`
In-memory or simple database logic for tracking the bill for each customer ID.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Test backend endpoints for adding/removing items from a cart explicitly via unit tests.
- Test frontend components rendering correctly with different cart states.

### Manual Verification
- We will run the frontend and backend locally.
- You can open the web app, enter a `customer_id`, and allow camera access.
- We will simulate "picking up" an item (e.g., showing a specific QR code or object to the camera) and verify it appears on your bill.
- We will simulate "putting back" that item and verify it is removed from your bill.
